As of the 2021-2022 academic year, the University of Michigan's out-of-state tuition and fees for undergraduate students are as follows:

$52,266 per year for students enrolled in the College of Literature, Science, and the Arts (LSA)
$54,238 per year for students enrolled in the College of Engineering
$54,538 per year for students enrolled in the Ross School of Business
$50,538 per year for students enrolled in the School of Information
Note that these figures do not include other expenses such as room and board, textbooks, and personal expenses, which can add several thousand dollars to the total cost of attendance.